Coordonate GPS
Diagram
Type anre:Position
Properties
content complex
minOccurs 0
maxOccurs 1
Model
Attributes
QName Type Use Annotation
geohash xs:string optional 
WGS84 GPS position encoded in 10 digits GeoHash as per https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geohash
 Example for Bucharest center: sxfsccrhnq
latitude xs:string optional 
Example latitude value for Bucharest center: 44.436339
longitude xs:string optional 
Example longitude value for Bucharest center: 26.102571
Source
 
<xs:element name="position" type="anre:Position" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">

    <xs:documentation>Coordonate GPS</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
</xs:element>

Attributes
QName Type Use Annotation
geohash xs:string optional 
WGS84 GPS position encoded in 10 digits GeoHash as per https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geohash
 Example for Bucharest center: sxfsccrhnq
latitude xs:string optional

Complex Type anre:Position
Namespace http://www.anre.ro/ANRESchema
Annotations
 
Coordinates must be in accordance
 with WGS84 and must use an ISO 6709 format as follows: [+/-]NN.NNNNNN.
Diagram
Used by
Elements anre:Address/position, anre:Position
Model
Attributes
QName Type Use Annotation
geohash xs:string optional 
WGS84 GPS position encoded in 10 digits GeoHash as per https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geohash
 Example for Bucharest center: sxfsccrhnq
latitude xs:string optional 
Example latitude value for Bucharest center: 44.436339
longitude xs:string optional 
Example longitude value for Bucharest center: 26.102571
Source
 
<xs:complexType name="Position">
  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>Coordinates must be in accordance&#xD;with WGS84 and must use an ISO 6709 format as follows: [+/-]NN.NNNNNN.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
  <xs:sequence/>
  <xs:attribute name="geohash" use="optional" type="xs:string">
    <xs:annotation>
